Place 1 teaspoon rosemary, the parsley, peppercorns and lemon in cheesecloth; tie securely. Heat broth and cheesecloth bag to boiling in 10-inch skillet; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. If fish filets are large, cut into 4 serving pieces. Place fish filets in skillet; add water, if necessary, to cover. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Remove fish to serving platter and keep warm. Reserve 1/3 cup broth mixture. Discard cheesecloth bag and remaining broth mixture. Mix half-and-half and cornstarch. Heat half-and-half mixture, reserved broth mixture, 1 teaspoon rosemary and the salt to boiling in skillet over medium heat. Boil and stir 1 minute. Pour over fish.